<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-10T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="15" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/213: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-11T12:00:00+08:00">May 11,
                                1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 11—2:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>519. Following from American Consul General at Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“May 10, 11 a.m. League Commission arrived here yesterday.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>